{"summary":"All five amendments identify real defects in the retry/backoff and process-backend changes. The four resume tests are now semantically broken and also unnecessarily slow without paused Tokio time; missing CLI binaries still flow through retryable classifications in the common availability/build-command paths; retry backoff is not cancellation-aware; and backend timeouts discard Codex/OpenRouter diagnostic artifacts instead of preserving them like other failures.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-1-2fc8a73c","decision":"accept","rationale":"`with_transient_failure(stage, 3)` means the stub fails the first 3 invocations and then succeeds. `RetryPolicy::default_policy()` now allows 5 attempts for `TransportFailure`, so these runs succeed on attempt 4 and `assert!(first_result.is_err())` is wrong. Raising the configured transient failures to 5 restores the intended exhausted-retries failure case."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-171fc893","decision":"accept","rationale":"These four tests use plain `#[tokio::test]` while the retry policy now applies real exponential backoff. In their current broken state they wait about 35 seconds per test before the fourth attempt succeeds; if the retry-count fix is applied they would wait even longer. `start_paused = true` is the correct test harness setting here and matches the existing retry/backoff tests in the file."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-5008e57c","decision":"accept","rationale":"The common missing-binary paths still produce `AppError::BackendUnavailable`, and `BackendUnavailable` is classified as `TransportFailure`, so workflow retries are still consumed when `claude` or `codex` is absent. `BinaryNotFound` currently only appears in narrower spawn/exit-127 paths, which does not satisfy the intended fast-fail behavior for the normal CLI-missing case. The missing-binary classification needs to propagate through availability and command construction as well."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-06c34f70","decision":"accept","rationale":"The retry loop computes `will_retry` once, logs the failure, and then does a plain `tokio::time::sleep(backoff).await`. If cancellation arrives during that sleep, the run remains stalled until the delay expires and only then observes cancellation at the next loop iteration. Making the backoff wait cancellation-aware is a real correctness and responsiveness fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-1-8b4ded53","decision":"accept","rationale":"Timeout errors returned from `spawn_and_wait()` currently go through `prepared.cleanup()`, which deletes Codex/OpenRouter temp artifacts, while non-zero exits and other terminal failures use `cleanup_failed_invocation()` and preserve them under `runtime/failed`. That makes hung or timed-out invocations less debuggable than ordinary failures. Timeout handling should use a preserving cleanup path too."}]}